      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): make Silent quick-create preset emit systemEvent payload",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen creating a cron job via the Control UI quick-create wizard with \"Silent\" delivery mode, pressing Create does nothing — the dialog stays open and no job is created. The root cause is a mismatch between the UI preset mapping and the backend validation: the quick-create dialog emits `payloadKind: \"agentTurn\"` for all presets, but the backend requires `payloadKind: \"systemEvent\"` when `sessionTarget` is `\"main\"` (which the Silent preset uses).\n\nThis fix adds `payloadKind: \"systemEvent\"` to the Silent preset mapping so the resulting job shape satisfies `assertSupportedJobSpec()` in the cron service. A focused regression test is included for the silent preset-to-payload mapping.\n\nFixes #95073\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Silent quick-create preset now produces a backend-compatible cron job shape (`payloadKind: \"systemEvent\"` with `sessionTarget: \"main\"`) instead of the rejected `\"agentTurn\"` + `\"main\"` combination.\n\n**Real environment tested**: Linux 6.8.0, Node 22.19, pnpm 11.2.2\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n```bash\ncd openclaw\npnpm test ui/src/ui/views/cron-quick-create.node.test.ts\npnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n```\n$ pnpm test ui/src/ui/views/cron-quick-create.node.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/lizeyu/workspace/issues-killer/openclaw\n\n ✓ cron quick create > silent preset emits systemEvent payload and targets main session\n ✓ cron quick create > keeps notify preset announce-capable by targeting an isolated session\n ✓ cron quick create > sets a valid scheduleAt for one-time presets\n ✓ cron quick create > clears deleteAfterRun and scheduleAt for recurring presets\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  4 passed (4)\n\n$ pnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.test.ts\n\n RUN  v4.1.8 /home/lizeyu/workspace/issues-killer/openclaw\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  40 passed (40)\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: The silent preset emits `payloadKind: \"systemEvent\"` and `sessionTarget: \"main\"`, which satisfies the backend's `assertSupportedJobSpec()` check (only `\"main\"` + `\"systemEvent\"` is allowed; `\"main\"` + `\"agentTurn\"` was rejected). All existing tests continue to pass.\n\n**What was not tested**: Full E2E test with a running Gateway and browser-based Control UI interaction. The fix is a pure data-transformation layer change in `draftToCronFormPatch()` and its correctness is directly covered by the unit test.\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n### Unit tests\n\n```\n$ pnpm test ui/src/ui/views/cron-quick-create.node.test.ts\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  4 passed (4)\n```\n\n### Regression\n\n```\n$ pnpm test ui/src/ui/controllers/cron.test.ts\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  40 passed (40)\n```\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] This change is backwards compatible — only affects the Silent quick-create preset; other presets and the advanced cron form are unchanged\n- [x] This change has been tested with existing configurations — no config changes involved\n- [ ] I have updated relevant documentation — N/A, the fix is internal to the UI preset mapping\n- [ ] Breaking changes (if any) are documented in Summary — no breaking changes\n\n## Current review state\n\n- [x] Self-review completed\n- [ ] At least one maintainer review\n- [ ] All CI checks passed\n",
